java: package javafx.application does not exist

- download openjavafx
https://gluonhq.com/products/javafx/

- set java version in Project Structure

- unzip and move to /Library/Java/javafx-sdk-14.0.2.1/lib
https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/javafx.html#vm-options

- add path (including /lib) to libraries

- in run configuration, add VM options:
--module-path /Library/Java/javafx-sdk-14.0.2.1/lib --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml

- fix permission in MacOS: General Settings, Security & Privacy: allow anyway

